cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new routing concept for SDNs. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the proposed approach is decentralized. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible category as the paper mentions integrity as one of the bottlenecks of SDNs. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the proposed approach involves management and control of the network. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper discusses multipath planning and address-equivalent naming mechanisms.
